:: Pub Music Sing
<<set $outside to 0>><<set $location to "pub">><<effects>>
<<set $weekly.pubMusic to true>>

You hum as you approach the <<person>>, much to <<his>> confusion. <<He>> slows, as if about to stop, but you begin to sing. <<His>> eyes widen slightly at the sound of your immaculate voice.
<br><br>

Without a word, <<he>> picks up where <<he>> left off, matching <<his>> rhythm to yours. The patrons' eyes are on you, amused by your performance.
<br><br>

<<if $seabird_lullaby gte 2 and random(0,100) is 1>>
	The <span class="teal">Seabird's Lullaby</span> crosses your mind. Following your memory, you hum the first notes of the song; it feels oddly natural. The <<person>> is unsure what to do, so <<he>> instead drops <<his>> instrument, content to listen to you.
	<br><br>
	Your voice lulls the audience. They fight to keep their eyes open. By the time you finish, most have fallen asleep, and the few who remain offer a hushed round of applause. You take your leave.
<<else>>
	<<switch random(1,2)>>
		<<case 1>>You reach the climax, and the <<person>> keeps up with rapture. You close your eyes and finish the song with a pitch so high it feels almost like a shriek. You take a moment to catch your breath. When you open your eyes, you find your audience bewildered, goosebumps rising on their skin. It's only natural. After all, they are the prey, and you are the hunter.
		<<case 2>>Your tune is languid yet mesmerising. The <<person>>'s pace aligns with yours. Closing your eyes and drawing out the last note, you finish the song. With a heavy sigh, you open your eyes and find your audience staring at you with dazed, but yearning expressions. Your ballad longs for a partner, and they must have felt it.
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>
	The room holds its breath for a heartbeat before bursting into a storm of applause. You take your leave.
<</if>>
<br><br>

Behind you, the <<person>> is showered with tips. <<His>> grateful gaze follows your back.
<<clearNPC pubMusic>>
<br><br>
<<link [[다음|Pub]]>><<endevent>><</link>>

