:: Pub Avery Stones
<<effects>>
"They're called wishing stones," Landry says. "Or clutching bones. Not sure if they're actually bones. Regardless, they're important to Avery."
<br><br>
"More importantly, these are fake. Here's my proposition. <span class="gold">I want you to infiltrate Avery's mansion, open <<nnpc_his "Avery">> vault, and replace the real stones with this forgery."</span> <<He>> folds the clothes over the fake stones, and pushes them towards you. "I know of only one other who's become close enough with Avery to reach <<nnpc_his "Avery">> inner sanctum. <<pShe>> did it by moving in with <<nnpc_him "Avery">>, and playing <<nnpc_his "Avery">> game."
<br><br>
<<person1>>
<<if C.npc.Avery.state is "dismissed">>
	"Easier said than done." <<He>> continues. "I heard you manage to shake <<nnpc_him "Avery">> off your tail. That's no matter. <span class="gold">Give <<nnpc_him "Avery">> this."</span> Landry reaches into <<his>> pocket, and produces a thin card in a protective case. <<He>> slides it across the table. It's from an old collectible game. "Should get your foot in the door. The rest will be up to you."
	<<set $avery_card_gift to true>>
	<br><br>
<</if>>
