:: Pub Avery Stones Ask
<<effects>>

<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
	"That sounds very dangerous," you say. "What do I get in return."
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"What's in it for me?" you ask.
<<else>>
	"What do I get in return?" you ask.
<</if>>
<br><br>

Landry pauses for a moment, thinking over <<his>> words. "<span class="blue">If you want to destroy Avery's ambitions,</span> then replace <<nnpc_his "Avery">> stones with mine. Avery's getting in with the wrong crowd. Dangerous people, though <<nnpc_he Avery>> doesn't realise it.
They've trusted <<nnpc_him "Avery">> with this artefact, or soon will. When the stones are revealed to be fake, their plans will crumble. There's no reward. If our goals align, they align, and we can work together. <span class="blue">Replace the stones, and Avery will be saved from <<nnpc_himself "Avery">>.</span>"
<br><br>

"It would also make some friends of mine very happy," <<he>> continues. "They're a bit out of touch I'm afraid. But they're strong. The sort your Bailey has to tiptoe around, or risk being crushed by. They have things, and do things, money can't buy. Friends like that would be good to have, no?"
<br><br>

<<He>> leans back. "I'm sure someone as enterprising as you will be able to squeeze Avery in other ways as well. Must be a lot of nice loot in that place. Though I shouldn't have to tell you this will be dangerous, and there's no rush. Avery plays a long game, and so do we."
<br><br>

"Thanks for indulging me. Now, what can I do for you?"
<br><br>

