			<<if $fake_artefact is "Avery">>
				<br><br>

				<<He>> seems to remember something. "Oh! Be careful what you say to Jordan. If you're too honest with <<nnpc_him "Jordan">>, <span class="blue"><<nnpc_he "Jordan">> might burn bridges with Avery regardless</span>. The Cloister has a habit of missing the forest for the fire."
			<</if>>
		<<case "Quinn">>
			"The next guest will be the mayor. It sounds important."
			<br><br>

			<<He>> perks up. "Perfect. Landry has someone on the inside, but they may have been compromised by personal attachment to Quinn."
			<<He>> shivers. "How anyone could grow attached to that porkslab is beyond me, but that's not important. They'll be in hiding.
			<span class="blue">You'll need to do something to get their attention first.</span> I loathe to ask this, but if you're very blunt with your intentions towards the mayor, you might get a reaction. You'll have to be sharp. No distractions."
			<br><br>

			<<He>> raises a hand. "When you see them, give them this hand signal."
			<<if $fake_artefact is "Avery">>
				<<He>> curves <<his>> hand upwards, before letting it fall in an arch.
			<<else>>
				<<He>> puts <<his>> thumb between each of <<his>> fingers in sequence, before flattening <<his>> hand and turning it.
			<</if>>
			"They just need a quick reminder of who they are, and who they're really working for."
		<<case "Remy">>
			"The next guest will be Remy, the farmer. From all the way out east."
			<br><br>

			<<if !$brownFoxWounded and $fake_artefact isnot "Avery">>
				<<He>> cups <<his>> hands together, and thinks for a long moment.
				<br><br>

				"The High Elk <<nnpc_himself "Remy">>." Another moment of silence. "<span class="blue">I'll be there.</span> I can't keep idling around here while they operate so boldly in the open."
			<<else>>
				<<He>> looks ashamed for a moment. "I was reckless last time. I won't make that mistake again.
				<<if $fake_artefact is "Avery">>
					It's time to let the elks get overconfident. The High Elk will likely have a pair of retainers with <<nnpc_him "Remy">>. <span class="blue">Make sure they don't leave the party,</span> no matter what."
				<<else>>
					It's time to humble the elks. The High Elk will likely have a pair of retainers with <<nnpc_him "Remy">>. <span class="blue">Make sure they leave the party early.</span> It should be easy to upset those snobbish types."
				<</if>>
			<</if>>
		<<case "Briar">>
			"The next guest will be Briar. Avery doesn't seem too happy about it."
			<br><br>

			<<if $fake_artefact is "Avery">>
				<<He>> thinks for a moment. "Briar has many underworld contacts. We might be able to convince <<nnpc_him "Briar">> to 'donate' some of <<nnpc_his "Briar">> stolen goods back." <<He>> smiles.
				"<span class="blue">Remind Briar that the most clever predators let their prey glut themselves first.</span>"
			<<else>>
				<<He>> thinks for a moment. "It'd be in our best interest to let Briar continue exactly as <<nnpc_he "Briar">> is. But... maybe we can give <<nnpc_him "Briar">> a push to go even further." <<He>> smiles.
				"<span class="blue">Stoke Briar's ego a little. Let Briar know just what Avery thinks of <<nnpc_him "Briar">>,</span> then build <<nnpc_him "Briar">> back up.
				Try to use subtle language, and talk like a criminal. Do you think you can pull that off?"
				<br><br>

				<<He>> looks over <<his>> shoulder at Landry, who gives a thumbs up. "Tell Briar to look for me <span class="gold">right under <<nnpc_his "Briar">> tail</span>. <<nnpc_He "Briar">>'ll know what it means."
			<</if>>
		<<case "Harper">>
			<<wearProp "phial red">>
			"The next guest will be doctor Harper."
			<br><br>

			A look of pure disdain crosses the third of <<his>> face that you can see. "The Cannibal Fox.
			<<if $fake_artefact is "Avery">>
				There's almost no way we can convince <<nnpc_him "Harper">> to cease support."
			<<else>>
				<<nnpc_He "Harper">> will surely support construction of the tower regardless."
			<</if>>
			<<His>> nails scratch the table.
			<br><br>

			"I won't lie to you. This request is a personal one. I'm putting a lot of trust in you." <<He>> reaches under <<his>> cloak, and produces two phials. One is filled with a murky green substance, while the other is a vibrant red.
			"The rabid fox will, as <<nnpc_he "Harper">> always does, make a meal out of <<nnpc_his "Harper">> kin. We're going to poison the meal. Whatever <<nnpc_he "Harper">> gives you, don't play along. Make sure whoever's in charge uses these."
			<br><br>

			<<He>> holds up the green phial. "This one is for the appetiser." <<He>> holds up the red in turn. "This is for the main course. One is a sedative and chemical marker, the other is concentrated wolfbrew.
			There's nothing we can do to stop <<nnpc_him "Harper">>. But we can at least grant the victims revenge. You'll understand soon, unfortunately."
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>
	<<set $avery_mansion.fox.task to $avery_mansion.guest>>
	<<set $avery_mansion.fox.task_detail to $fake_artefact is "Avery" ? "ascend" : "descend">>
	<<if $avery_mansion.guest is "Remy" and !$brownFoxWounded and $fake_artefact isnot "Avery">>
	<<else>>
		<span class="gold">The brown fox's request has been added to your journal.</span>
		<br><br>
	<</if>>
<</if>>

<<set $phase to 0>>

<<brownFoxOptions>>

:: Pub Brown Fox Dungeon
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
	"I found the vault. It's in a... dungeon. The entrance is hidden somewhere in Avery's study.
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"I found the vault. It's in Avery's rape dungeon, the entrance of which is hidden somewhere in Avery's study.
<<else>>
	"I found the vault. It's in a dungeon, the entrance of which is hidden somewhere in Avery's study.
<</if>>
It's locked by a keypad with a four-digit combination."
<br><br>

<<His>> green eyes widen behind <<his>> mask. "Perfect. We're that much closer."
<<if $avery_mansion.fox.progress lt 12>>
	<<if $brownFoxWoundedTimer>>
		<<He>> looks down at <<his>> leg in annoyance.
	<<else>>
		<<He>> thinks for a moment.
	<</if>>
	"Getting into a vault like that won't be easy. <span class="green">Maybe we can work together to break in.</span> I'll need a few more favours first, though. There's more information we need."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<brownFoxOptions>>

:: Pub Brown Fox Stones
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
"Take a look." You hold out the stones.
<br><br>

<<He>> stares down at them. After a moment, <<he>> grows a wide smile. "You've done a very good thing. The plan is set, and their ritual will backfire.
With the right subterfuge, we can <span class="green">speed up the construction of the tower</span>, and get this whole ordeal over with sooner."
<br><br>

<<He>> looks down. "I've heard stories. I can't imagine it's been easy living with Avery. You'll have your pound of flesh soon." <<He>> covers <<his>> mouth. "I'm sorry, that was a terrible choice of words."
<br><br>

<<brownFoxOptions>>

:: Pub Brown Fox Revealed
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
	"Is that you, Gwylan?"
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"I know it's you, Gwylan."
<<else>>
	"I didn't think this was how you operated, Gwylan."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> stares at you for a moment, then giggles. "I thought you'd never catch on. What gave it away?"
<br><br>

<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("romance")>>
	"I could practically feel it," you say. "I know your smell, too."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> blushes, and tries to suppress looking giddy with limited success. "Aww, aren't you a sweetheart."
<<elseif $brownFoxWoundedHint>>
	"I saw the <<if _gwylanStatus.includes("wounded")>>bandages<<else>>scar<</if>> on your leg," you say. "It's a bit too much of a coincidence."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> nods. "I knew you were sharp. It's not like I could hide it forever."
<<else>>
	"I know you," you say simply. "Did you think I'd forget?"
	<br><br>

	<<He>> frowns. "Most do." <<He>> places <<his>> hand on <<his>> head. "So it was the hypnosis, then. How troublesome."
<</if>>
<<He>> leans back in <<his>> seat. "Regardless, that's not who I am right now. Keep it secret for me, would you, <<pcpetname "Gwylan">>?"
<br><br>

<<if $brownFoxCoverBlown>>
	You open your mouth to speak, but <<he>> interrupts you.
	<<if _gwylanStatus.includes("cautious")>>
		"Surely you don't want to blow my cover again. You'll owe me for that, dear. My leg still aches where the High Elk stabbed me."
	<<else>>
		"Surely you don't want to blow my cover again. My leg still aches where the High Elk stabbed me." <<He>> looks serious for only a moment, and starts smiling again. "It's alright. You've already more than made up for it."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
<</if>>

<<brownFoxOptions>>

:: Pub Brown Fox Apologise
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
"Look, I'm sorry about—"
<br><br>

<<He>> shushes you.
<br><br>

"Not right now. Let's keep such things out of business. This is bigger than both of us." A long moment of silence passes. "If... if you want to talk after we're done, I'll be over there." <<He>> points back to <<his>> original table.
<br><br>

<<brownFoxOptions>>

:: Pub Brown Fox Unavailable
<<effects>>
<<if isGwylanAbsent() is "nobody">>
	You ask for nobody.
	<br><br>

	Landry gives you a confused look.
<<else>>
	You ask for the brown fox.
	<br><br>

	Landry shakes <<his>> head. "Haven't heard from <<nnpc_him Gwylan>>. <<nnpc_He Gwylan>> might have been compromised. You may just have to continue on without <<nnpc_him Gwylan>>."
<</if>>
<br><br>

