:: Pub Avery Stones Tell
<<effects>>

<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
	"It was hard," you say. "But I managed to replace Avery's stones."
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"I replaced Avery's stones," you say. "It wasn't difficult."
<<else>>
	"I got into Avery's vault," you say. "And replaced <<nnpc_his Avery>> stones with yours."
<</if>>
<br><br>

Landry smiles as <<he>> pulls out a flip phone and dials something into it. "Very nice work. Now we just need to wait for Avery to finish that building of <<nnpc_hers Avery>> on Elk Street. <<nnpc_He Avery>>'ll need the stones for the opening ceremony. When <<nnpc_he Avery>> can't produce them, <<nnpc_his Avery>> plans will blow up in <<nnpc_his Avery>> face."
<br><br>

<<He>> looks you over for a moment. "Would you mind showing the real ones to me?" You look around, and hold them out to Landry.
<br><br>

Landry just looks at the stones for a moment, transfixed as if in wonder. "To be honest," <<he>> says. "I didn't think you'd find them. I'll put in a good word for you." <<He>> smiles. "You've done a very good thing."
<br><br>

<<He>> reaches for the bones, but hesitates. "Those really are bones." <<He>> peers at them. "Let's hope they're from an animal, eh?" <<He>> reaches into <<his>> pocket, and produces a magnifying glass. <<His>> smile broadens. "There's a code etched into the bone. As I thought. Wish they had hidden it somewhere less gristly."
<br><br>

Landry hands the stones back to you. "The brown fox insisted that you should hold onto those when you find them.<<if !$avery_mansion.fox.stones>> Speaking of, you should tell <<nnpc_him Gwylan>> yourself. I'd love to see the look on <<nnpc_his Gwylan>> face.<</if>>"
<br><br>

