	You left quite the impression on <<him>>. Said you were very brave. <span class="green">I have a feeling that you two are going to be seeing a lot more of each other very soon.</span>"
<<else>>
	<<He>> smiles. <<person2>>
	<<if $avery_mansion.fox.saved and !$avery_mansion.fox.end>>
		"<<Hes>> alright, but <<hes>> gone off the grid.
	<<else>>
		"<<Hes>> gone off the grid.
	<</if>>
	<<if $avery_mansion.fox.friend>>
		You left quite the impression on <<him>>.
		<<if !$avery_mansion.fox.end>>
			<<if $avery_mansion_fire_time>>
				If you want to say goodbye, <span class="blue">wait for the fire at Avery's mansion to burn out, and look around there at night.</span> <<Hes>> bound to skulk around the ruins looking for something or another.
			<<else>>
				If you want to say goodbye, <span class="blue">take a look around the ruins of the manor at night.</span> <<Hes>> bound to skulk around there, looking for something or another.
			<</if>>
			<span class="green">I have a feeling that you two are going to be seeing a lot more of each other very soon.</span>"
		<<else>>
			<<He>> was pretty torn up about you getting hurt, but <span class="green">I have a feeling that you two are going to be seeing a lot more of each other very soon.</span>"
		<</if>>
	<<else>>
		Didn't say much, but seemed happy enough that the job was done. <span class="teal">Maybe you'll see each other again soon.</span>"
	<</if>>
